## Part 1 — 🐛 Bug Fix: Notifications Not Firing

### Root Cause Analysis

**The bug is in [`schedule_screen.dart`](file:///e:/2026/MyBigProjects_SimpleLib/TrackerTime/lib/features/schedule/presentation/schedule_screen.dart) — the form has no date picker, only a time picker.**

```dart
// Line 348 — _startTime is initialized as "now + 30 min"
_startTime = appt?.startTime ?? DateTime.now().add(const Duration(minutes: 30));

// Line 356 — _selectTime only picks hour:minute, never changes the DATE
Future<void> _selectTime(BuildContext context) async {
  final TimeOfDay? time = await showTimePicker(...);
  if (time != null) {
    setState(() {
      _startTime = DateTime(
        _startTime.year, _startTime.month, _startTime.day,  // ← DATE STAYS TODAY
        time.hour, time.minute,
      );
    });
  }
}
```

**Result:** If the user picks a time like `9:00 AM` after `9:00 AM` has already passed today, `scheduledDate.isAfter(now)` in [`notification_service.dart`](file:///e:/2026/MyBigProjects_SimpleLib/TrackerTime/lib/core/services/notification_service.dart) Line 142 returns `false` → notification is **silently skipped**.

**Secondary cause:** Android 12+ requires `SCHEDULE_EXACT_ALARM` permission in `AndroidManifest.xml` for `exactAllowWhileIdle` to work.

---

### Fix 1A — Add Date Picker to Schedule Form

#### [MODIFY] [schedule_screen.dart](file:///e:/2026/MyBigProjects_SimpleLib/TrackerTime/lib/features/schedule/presentation/schedule_screen.dart)

Replace the time-only `ListTile` with a two-row date + time picker:

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Start Date    [Mon, July 21 2026]  📅    │  ← showDatePicker
│ Start Time    [09:00 AM]           🕘    │  ← showTimePicker (existing)
└──────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

- `_selectDate()` → calls `showDatePicker` with `firstDate: DateTime.now()` (prevents past dates for 'once' appointments).
- After date+time both picked → the notification will always be in the future.

### Fix 1B — Add Fallback to `inexactAllowWhileIdle`

#### [MODIFY] [notification_service.dart](file:///e:/2026/MyBigProjects_SimpleLib/TrackerTime/lib/core/services/notification_service.dart)

Wrap every `zonedSchedule` call in a try-catch with an `inexactAllowWhileIdle` fallback (same pattern as TrackerMoney):

```dart
try {
  await _localNotifications.zonedSchedule(
    ...,
    androidScheduleMode: AndroidScheduleMode.exactAllowWhileIdle,
  );
} catch (_) {
  await _localNotifications.zonedSchedule(
    ...,
    androidScheduleMode: AndroidScheduleMode.inexactAllowWhileIdle,
  );
}
```

### Fix 1C — Android Manifest Permission

#### [MODIFY] `android/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml`

Add the exact alarm permission (required Android 12+):

```xml
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.SCHEDULE_EXACT_ALARM"/>
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.USE_EXACT_ALARM"/>
```

And add `requestExactAlarmsPermission()` call in `NotificationService.requestPermissions()`.

